澳大利亚出产大量的扁豆。<ref name="ABC-Lentils">{{cite web | url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2010-02-26/humble-lentil-turns-into-cash-crop/344970 | title=Humble lentil turns into cash crop | publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation | date=February 28, 2010 | accessdate=April 4, 2012 | author=Staight, Kerry | archive-date=2016-10-30 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030082007/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2010-02-26/humble-lentil-turns-into-cash-crop/344970 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.abc.net.au/landline/stories/s99108.htm | title=Lentils offer farmers a better cash crop alternative | publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation (Landline) | date=February 13, 2000 | accessdate=April 4, 2012 | author=Courtney, Pip | author-link=Pip Courtney | archive-date=2014-05-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140527081934/http://www.abc.net.au/landline/stories/s99108.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>据估计，2010年澳大利亚将生产约14.3万吨扁豆。<ref name="ABC-Lentils"/>澳大利亚大部分的扁豆收成都出口到印度次大陆和中东。<ref name="ABC-Lentils"/>

=== 意大利 ===
1950年，意大利的南方基金促使政府实施奖励措施，种植西红柿、烟草和柑橘类水果等经济作物。结果，他们造成了这些作物的过剩，导致这些作物在全球市场上的过度饱和。这导致这些作物的价值下降。

